betterquesting:10.desc:8: Look around in the crates for a way to open the door!

This pack features a lot of custom structures with loot, each structures contains a great amount of loot, I recommend you check them out!

All of the structures were made by the community so you can submit your own as well.
Starting out with nothing, you have to get yourself kitted out. No punching trees! Make yourself at home and loot everything you find; Tools, Plants,§4 Everything!

You can find some crystals in the station.

§c§4Red Crystals §fcan be used for fuel to smelt 32 items each.

§a§4Green Crystals §fcan be used for various alloys to transfer power etc.

You can find some starter tools in the station, all of them are very useful but they are only just better than naff. You can get an upgrade later.

§7§9§8§4The Hammer §facts as a pickaxe, you can also use it to muffle the sound of some machines
§4The Crowbar§f can be used to salvage hull blocks.
§8§4The Screwdriver §fcan be used for configuring GT Covers, you can also directly Shift-Right Click the covers but the benefit of the screwdriver is that you can access the cover from any side.
§8§4The Wrench §fis an engineer's best friend, you can use it to set that output side of machines and is also the tool you need to break them.

I recommend having all the tools on you most of the time.

You will find some hull blocks in the station, you can salvage some of the blocks by shift right clicking with your Crowbar in the station's hallways for different resources.
That's how you'll be able to get most of the resources necessary in this stage.

§8§4Sturdy Hulls§f can be used to make Iron & Tin
§e§6§4Rusty Hulls§f can be used to make Copper & Tin
§7Rusty Scaffolds§f can be used to get Simple Internals which you can use to get Redstone & Coal Dust
You get a space suit when you enter the station. You can use it to explore for a while before you run out of oxygen. You can fill it up with oxygen later but this will have to do for a while.
This is one of the key Multiblocks in Gregtech, and at this stage it unlocks the MV Tier Material.

With your trusty crowbar and hulls you can get to work and get some §4Hull Plates§f. You can use them to make some§4 Plating Components§f or scrap them on the ground to get pieces of §4Broken Scrap§f.

Start your journey in §4Cosmic Chaos§f!

Create a station using §6/station create§f
Invite another player to your station using §6/station invite [name]§f
Join another player's station using §6/station join§f

Smash your §4Hull Plates §f& §4Internals §fon the ground to get Pieces of §5§4Broken Scrap§f & new materials.
You can smelt the Pieces of §4Broken Scrap §fto get their §4Ingot §fcounterparts.
You will also get §4Redstone§f &§4 Small Piles of Coal Dust§f from smashing the§4 Simple Internals§f on the ground.

Can be found in the Night Plains.

This can be filtered down into usable parts for circuit crafting!

Make a §4Crafting Station§f using your Simple Internals & Hull Plates.
The Crafting Station unlocks §43x3 Crafting,§f You can put your tools in there aswell for better inventory management and It can also pull items from inventories next to it like crates & chests.
You should probably make some extra tools just for crafting.

Convenient!

With your Space Suit it is worth to take a peek at other areas on the station.

You are safe to be in the §8§4Processing Sector §fwhich is right in the middle of the station since it is safely sealed off and the oxygen vent can provide enough O2 to not 

All the other areas of the station are closed off with red blocks to avoid suffocation, however you can use your §4Space Suit§f to get around those areas just fine. Do note that the time you can spend there is limitted by how much O2 you have available, that is visible through the §4O2 Bar HUD§f above your Food bar on your screen.

On the left you have the §8§4Mining Sector §fwhich is the biggest sector on the station by far, but it is highly damaged. There you can find an abundance of crystals and Hull Blocks, The loot is also pretty good with a decent amount of pre-made components & fluids, You can also find a §8§4Diamond Screwdriver §fwhich is very durable.


To the right of the Processing Sector you can find the§4 Main Hub §fwhich has been mostly cut off from the station but from what remains of it you can find some pre-made components and fluids there, You can also find a §4Statinless Steel Hammer§f which is very durable as well.

If you go straight across the Processing Sector, you should be able to find the §4Compactor Workshop§f, You can find some pre-made components and fluids here along with some components from the rocket, but most importantly here is where the§4 Trash Compactor§f lies, although it is broken you should be able to repair it fairly easily & get it running, Good Luck!

The Quest Book has different themes you can choose based on your personal preference, You can choose them from the main Quest Book menu under the themes tab.

This pack has a new Quest Book theme: §k§k§l§l§d§c§a§8§f§e§d§c§a§2§8§7§d§9§8"Reinforced Neon"

With some Plating Components you can make a §4Furnace§f, You can use the furnace and smelt the Broken Scraps you got earlier.

For fuel you can use§4 Small Piles of Coal Dust§f acquired through smashing Simple Internals or alternatively use §4Red Crystal Shards§f scattered all over the station, you will have to be more careful not to waste any fuel though.

With smelting Broken Scrap Parts you will get their §4Ingot counterparts§f.

You can also smelt iron ingots to get §4Wrought Iron§f which will be key for progressing through this chapter.

You can also use it to make better and more durable tools.

Before going into other areas of the station, you should prepare some airlock doors, there are other ways to do this but perhaps the most fancy way is using §4Small Airlock Doors §f&§4 Iron Buttons§f.

If you're playing on a team I suggest you make a Quest Book Party; You can access that in the main quest book menu under the Party tab.

The benefit of that is you don't need to do everything multiple times and you will get multiple rewards from completing a single quest, Who doesn't like free stuff?
Throughout your playthrough you will receive some Currency from completing quests; You will be able to trade the currency into materials to ease progression.
You can toggle the Quest Book view mode on the left of the quest menu to only see quests in the main progression line as oppose to everything including optional quests.

Here are some ways to contact and support the developers of the pack, connect with other players and hang out.

Curseforge Page:

The quest book will guide you through the progression of the pack. if you're ever stuck, check the questbook.

The One Probe is a very handy mod that can tell you basic information about a block you're looking at.
It is at the top of your screen by default, You can also change the positioning and the size with the §6/topcfg §fcommand.
Just Enough Items is the source of most of your information along with this quest book, it is the menu on the right of your screen that will tell you the uses and recipes of anything.

You can use Green Crystal Alloy & Silver to make some §4Crystal Batteries§f.

They are pretty much crucial to a power system.

You can put them inside Battery Buffers for them to work.

They are the replacement to Rusty Batteries.

Notable Biomes:

§5The Midnight:§r

-Crystal Spires: §dBloom Crystal§r
-Obscured Plateau: §9Archic Shards§r
-Warped Fields: §1Dark Water§r
-Fungi Forest: §aTall Mushrooms§r
-Vigilant Forest: §bSuavis§r
-Night Plains: §5Miasma§r

§aThe Betweenlands:§r

-Swamplands: §aGiant Weedwood Trees§r with §2Dentrothyst§r inside
-Swamplands Clearing: §6Tree Sprits§r

-Sludge Plains: §cMiddle Gem Ores§r, §8Tar§r, and §eSludge§r
-Sludge Plains Clearing:§6 The Sludgeon§r

-Coarse Islands: §eGiant Roots§r and §6Cragrock Towers§r
-Raised Isles: §6Chiromaw Matriarch Nests§r and §6Cragrock Towers§r

-Deep Waters: §7Cragrock Spires§r, which have §eBarnacle Clusters§r growing an them

Homes are enabled in this pack, You can choose to not use them if you feel they are too cheaty but that's up to you.

Use §6/sethome [name]§f to set a home at your location.
Use §6/home [name]§f to teleport to your home.

Note that homes only work if you are in §4the same dimension as your home§f.

With either §4Iron§f or §4Wrought Iron§f you can make some new and more durable tools.

§4The Saw§f can be used as an Axe or A Weapon, you can also use it to make bolts, sheets, springs or pipes.
§4The File§f can be used to make springs, rods, tool heads or screws.
§4The Wire Cutter§f can be used to connect, disconnect or break wires & cables, you can also use it to make wires, fine wires, springs, small gears and more.

With these, you'll be able to assemble the §4Recycler§f and start making more complex materials!

§6§fYou can see how any of these multiblocks are formed if you check uses in §4JEI§f on the controller block, or §4Shift-Right click§f on the multiblock in world; §4each successive click will alter the hologram§f.§r

The Recycler is a §4very good alternative§f to manually scrapping your hull blocks and plates with a crowbar.

You will also be able to use it to §4crush your ingots into dust for alloys§f.

Place the §b§f§4ULV Battery Buffer§r next to the §e§fULV Energy Hatch§r and rotate it by using a §9§fWrench§r on the rectangle section closest to the Hatch. After placing some §6§f§4Rusty Batteries§r§r inside, you'll be able to run the Station Recycler!

As the Recycler runs, it will collect contaminants and eject them from the top in the form of §c§fRed§r, §a§fGreen§r, or §9§fBlue§r Crystals. It will §4stop§f when the crystal is fully grown.

You'll need more output hatches to process the materials with§4 more than one§f output type.

Until you can craft conveyors & pumps on your own, you'll have to rely on good old fasioned looting.

You can make §4Tin Item Pipes§f with Tin Plates(Surprise!).
You can also make §4Bronze Fluid Pipes§f with §4Bronze Plates§f.

Item Pipes §9§rdo not pull§r, but they will push any item inserted into them to other connected inventories, prioritizing §9§rthe closest§r first.

You can §4Shift-Right Click with a Wrench§f on an Item/Fluid Pipe to make it §4Mono-Directional§f, meaning if an item goes in that pipe it will not try to come back. This is indicated on the pipe with a §4Light Gray/Gray§4§k§f ring around the pipe, You will have to make sure that the ring is on the side of the pipe closest to where the §4contents' destination are§f.
Imagine that -] is the pipe, : is the conveyor and ] is the ring.
Input -------> Output
Input :-]-]-]-]> Output
You §4do not have to §funderstand this function to be able to effectively use pipes but it makes it a lot easier to troubleshoot things.
This behaviour is especially useful for §4Fluid Pipes§f or areas where you have multiple Inputs.

Right now, you can use pipes with §6§4Conveyor Modules§r, §4Output Buses§f and §4Machine Auto-Outputs§f all in the ULV age.

Place a §6§4Conveyor§r on the connection between a pipe and the inventory you want it to interact with. 
The rectangles you see when holding a cover and looking at a pipe represent the sides of the pipe, this applies to all GT machines(the corners represent the opposite face of the machine you are looking at).

If you want to §4extract§f items/fluids from an inventory, you'll need to set the §6§rConveyor§r/Pump to Import mode with a §a§r§4Screwdriver§f or §4directly Shift-Right Click§f on the Cover§r.

§9§rPlacing pipes(or wires) against a block will place it with a connection already connected to that face. You'll need a §9§4Tool§r to configure additional connections. §9§4Wrench§r for Pipes/Machines, and a §e§4Wirecutter§r for Wires/Cables.

Using the Station Recycler you can now get §4much better yield§f out§f of scrapping hulls.

Instead of just getting Pieces of Broken Scrap, You will now acquire Scrap Dust, You can either directly smelt this to get Iron & Copper or separate the Tin using an §4Electromagnetic Separator§f.

With the Station Recycler you now have access to §4Blue Crystals§f.

Although it is not as useful as it's Red & Green counterparts, It is still a very crucial component to §4Blue Alloy§e§f, which is an alloy that has many uses, such as §4The Blue Alloy Hook§f.

Simple Internals contain a large amount of §4Rubber§f, You can recycle them to extract the rubber out of them. By doing so you will also get A lot of §4Redstone§f &§4 Glass Dust§f as well.

The process to successfully get usable §4Rubber Bars§f out of Rubber Scraps is not too hard.

First reycle the §4Simple Internals§f acquired from recycling different hull blocks, You will get§4 Rubber Scrap§f from this process, then you need to recycle the the Rubber Scraps again to acquire §4Small Piles of Rubber Pulp§f, You can then compress 4 Small Piles of Rubber Pulp into 1 §3§4Rubber Pulp§f, and by smelting them in a furnace you will now acquire §4Rubber Bars§f.

Rubber has a lot of different uses, But perhaps the most common one is §4coating wires with it§f which will make wires have less loss and not damage you if you get close to them.

You can now acquire various §6Alloys§f that do their job better than their purer ingredients.

§4Bronze§f is a sturdy alloy from Copper & Tin, You can get 3 Bronze Ingots from 3 Copper Ingots + 1 Tin Ingot.
§4Red Alloy§f is a highly conductant alloy from Copper & Redstone, You can get 1 Red Alloy Ingot from 1 Copper Ingot + 4 Redstone Dust
§4Tin Alloy§f is a cheap yet sturdy from Tin & Iron, You can get 2 Tin Alloy Ingots from 1 Iron Ingot + 1 Tin Ingot.
§aGreen Crystal Alloy§r is a very conductant alloy from Green Crystals & Crude Steel, You can get 5 Green Crystal Alloy Ingots from 1 Green Crystal Dust + 4 Crude Steel Ingots, It's significance compared to Red Alloy is that it can supply Double the Amperage and can also act as a capacitor.§4

The Station Recycler unlocks the possibility to recycle§4 Crude Steel§f from Tough Hulls.

You can use the Recycler to get §4Dense Hull Plates§f, After you crush them, You will get §4Dense Scrap Dust§f, Which can then be smelted to get §4Crude Steel Ingots§f.

You can also alternatively use the Electromagnetic Separator to separate §4Lead dust§f from the Dense Scrap Dust as a byproduct.

By using the Steel Crates scattered around the station you have probably ensured yourself a good amount of storage,

If not you can make more §4Bronze Crates§f or §4Bronze Drums§f, You will also need them in different recipes such as Output/Input Busses.

GT Crates & Drums also have the benefit of being able to interact with GT Covers.

This is a mechanic put in place for gaining extra information from quests, at each major progression chapter you will need unique items to get information about more specific details of a process/task.

With production of Crude Steel & Rubber it is a good time to make some §4New Tools§f and maybe upgrade your older ones to Crude Steel.

§4The Crowbar§f is used to take off Covers from GT Blocks.

§4The Mortar§f can be used to crush ingots into dust without the need of the Station Recycler, but it is fragile and breaks fairly quickly.

§4The Soft Hammer§f can be used to toggle machines ON & OFF with a single click.

§4The Plunger§f can be used to drain fluids from your machines; Right Click to drain 1 Bucket worth of liquid from the output slot, Shift-Right Click to drain 1 Bucket of liquid from the input slot(Only works with GT Machines).

§4The Knife§f is used to cut food into smaller pieces, it also doubles as a weapon. You can also use it to turn rubber plates into rings and is used later for multiblock maintanence.

With some Complex Internals you can now automate the production of Mushrooms.

§4The Spores Recreator§f runs with 10 RF/t and every 40 Ticks, it creates 2 Mushrooms from 1 Mushroom & 500L of water.

You will have to cycle the mushrooms back to the input slot for it to run constantly.

You can find Mushrooms in the Station.

Now that you have access to rubber you can now make your own §4Machine Covers§f.

Machine Covers are very useful, and you will probably use them a lot.

Think of them as modifiers/upgrades to machines, if you add one to a side it will add a functionality to that side.

§4Motors §f&§4 Pistons§f are only Crafting Components but§4 Pumps§f, §4Conveyors §f& §4Robot Arms§f come with functions.

§4Conveyors§f can transport items, they Auto-Input/Pull/Import & they can also Auto-Output/Push/Export, You can change that behaviour using a Screwdriver or directly Shift-Right Clicking the Conveyor, You can also change their item transportation speed. Additionally you can filter them with an Item Filter.

§4Pumps§f can transport fluids just like Conveyors can transport items.

§4Robot Arms§f can also transport items but they can also regulate how many items are in the Input/Output inventory and how many items can go through at once. It has 3 different modes:

§4Transfer Any§f: The Robot Arm will act just like a conveyor in this mode.
§4Supply Exact§f: Ensures that only a specific amount of items will go through, No more, No Less. For example if set to 3 Items, it will only transfer 3 Items at a time, even if there are 2 Items available for it, in that case it will just leave the 2 in the input inventory until more items get added to it.
§4Keep Exact§f: Will fill Output Inventory until it reaches a specified number of items at that point the robot arm will stop working.

§4Regulators§f can transfer liquids like Robot Arms

GT Covers are §4TPS Friendly§f meaning whatever your TPS is they will work the same way, they do that by working in real time rather than checking your games tick time, this way they will also hurt your TPS by much smaller amounts.

You can find some §4Framed Drawers§f in the Station, They are very useful for bulk item storage, Each Drawer can fit §432 total stacks of items inside§f.

You can also craft some §4Fluid Tanks§f from EnderIO, they have less storage than Bronze Drums, but you can fill them with water quite easily using the Evertide Amulet also found in the station, you can also automate cycling the Amulet in and out of the tank with a conveyor cycle.

Using some Alloys & Rubber you can make an §4Electromagnetic Separator§f, It can be used for better scrap processing, to get some new materials, albeit very slowly.

You can get §7Tin§r from Separating Iron/Copper from Heavy/Light Scrap dust.
You can also get §dLead§f from Separating Crude Steel from Dense Scrap dust.

You can either connect a cable line to power both the recycler and the Separator or you can also just rotate the Battery Buffer when you need to.

You can now make an acutal §4Crowbar§f, this Crowbar has the ability to be able to salvage from White Tough Hulls, Which can give you §4Silver Ingots§f.

You can also get §4Complex Internals§f which can be used for a couple different machines.

You can now upgrade your furnaces to §4Silver Furnaces§f.

They are faster.. lol

Using a §4Water Electrolyzer§f you can create §4Hydrogen §f&§4 Oxygen§f.

You can use them for various chemical processes but you can also use§4 Oxygen§f to fill up your Space Suit again; You will need a Gas Charge Pad though.

I strongly recommend you set up a big buffer for Hydrogen, because you will get a lot of it.

A §aSuit Workbench§f is needed to modify your suit, you can also add more tanks to your suit.

You can fill a §9Gas Charge Pad§f with Oxygen and then Stand atop it to charge your suit with O2.
You can do the same for the §6Suit Jetpack§f, but with §9Hydrogen§r.

You can also make a bigger pressure tank using Crude Steel.

§4Potin§f is a light material made from Copper, Tin & Lead.

It's main usage is §4Fluid Pipes§f, it provides cheap yet fast fluid pipes.

You can now make your first §4LV Circuits§f.

These will come in very handy in a bit.

If you are playing the pack with a team, I would recommend you do some extra steps before starting your playthrough.

Check the quest about Quest Book Parties.

Make an FTB Teams team through the GUI for FTB Teams, you can find that on the top left of your screen when you open your inventory.

Run the command for Extra Utilities 2 GP Sharing: §6/xu_powersharing§f and select your teammate.

You can use Blue Crystal Shard Dust with Silver to create §4Blue Alloy§f.

1 Blue Crystal Shard Dust + 2 Silver Dust = 2 Blue Alloy Dust

You can also use the Blue Alloy to create the §4Blue Alloy Hook§f, It's a very versatile tool for very easy mobility. 

It also goes along very well with the §4Suit Jetpack§f.

Once you have the §4Generator§f back up and running, you'll be able to process materials much more efficiently and with less stress.

You might be able to find a few drums partially filled with some §aBiomass§f around the station to get you started.

It is highly recommended to have some energy buffer stored in batteries.

§6§fThis produces 2 Amps of ULV power, so you will need at least a 2x cable of Red or 1x Green Alloy Cable to transfer power from the Dynamo.

Welcome to §4Cosmic Chaos§f! The pack is a space themed adventure & automation pack.
Explore new planets and environments; Overcome challenges; Design a factory; Discover, Create and beat the Cosmic Chaos!

If you end up getting low on power, you'll be able to keep the lights on with the §4Hand Crank Generator§f.

You can find the §6Primitive Stator§f in the station.

Using some blueprints found in the station you can make a §4NASA Slow Cooker§f.

§e§fThis is how you'll do most chemical processes.

Over time, the Vents will clog up with §4Sulfur §for§4 Carbon dust§f. You can remove them simply by Shift-Right Clicking the Exhaust Vents.

It's highly recommended to make an extra NASA Slow Cooker as soon as you can, and leave this one just for the automation of power.

Now that you have access to crude steel you can make §4LV Machine Hulls§f.

It doesn't have much use to you right now, But you can make an §4LV Output Bus§f to have up to 4 Output slots.

No more bus spam!

You can replace the exhaust vents on the NASA Slow Cooker with §4Silver Exhaust Vents§f.

This will §4prevent the multiblock from clogging up and stopping work§f.

Do note that §4all §fthe exhaust vents need to be clogged for the Slow Cooker to stop work, So you only need to replace one of them with a silver one to have a well maintained multiblock while also getting the Sulfur & Carbon dust.

For automating power production in the station you will need to have a steady supply of §2Mushrooms §f& §9Water§f.
Both of these are very easily automatable, You need to then automatically process them into §aBiomass§f which can then be directly transported to your §4Backup Generator§f to be turned into §ePower§f.

All of these are beneficial to have storage of; You can use Drawers for Mushrooms, Drums for Water & Biomass, and Battery Storage for power.

OK so first off; GT Power is very different to all other mods with an energy mechanic.

GT Power is divided into different §4voltage tiers§f; Each Voltage Tier has a Maximum Voltage it can support.

Tier Name - Tier Full Name - Maximum Voltage(EU)
ULV - Ultra Low Voltage - §48§f
LV - Low Voltage -§4 32§f
MV - Medium Voltage -§4 128§f
HV - High Voltage -§4 512§f
EV - Extreme Voltage - §42048§f
IV - Insane Voltage - §48192§f
LuV - Ludicrous Voltage -§4 32768§f§f
ZPMV - Zero Point Module Voltage -§4 131072§f
UV - Ultimate Voltage -§4 524288§f
...
§4Maximum Voltage of a tier = (4^n)*8; Starting from n=0=ULV§f

Along with different voltages, you can also have §4different current(amperage) values§f; Think of them as packets that transfer your voltage.

2 Amperes of ULV Power is 16 EU and 4 Amperes of ULV Power is 1 Ampere of LV Power.

Keep in mind that Current can only be an§4 integer§f so: 28 EU is 3 Amperes of ULV Energy + 4 EU, If a source was to output 28 EU it will do 3 Amps of ULV and then leave the 4 EU behind for later use. 

That's also the exact logic behind§4 GT Transformers§f, This logic will not work without the usage of transformers though. The machine will either explode if the Voltage Tier is too high or just not work if the voltage tier is not sufficient to it's recipe.

If the Voltage Tier passing through a cable is §4too high§f, no matter the current(because of the reason mentioned below); the cable will get §4too hot and burn§f.

Machines and cables §4will only take the amount of amperage they need and can take§f, so do not worry about your 1x cables burning because they were connected to a 4A energy source. but if it is connected to a 4A Energy sink you will have to worry about it because you are §4not supplying enough energy to i§f§4t§f.

Along with Voltage & Current there is also a mechanic called §4Loss§f.

You do not have to worry about Loss in this stage because it is fairly simple to make lossless cables such as Red Alloy & Green Crystal Alloy.

In later stages however it will be a mechanic that you'll need to pay attention to, as it's not as simple to create Lossless Cables(Superconductors).

Loss has 3 Factors; §4Distance§f, §4Current§f, §4Loss Constant§f
Let's talk about a §44x Tin Cable§f for example, They can transfer §44A of LV Energy§f and have a loss of §41 EU/Ampere/Block§k§f.
Imagine you are running §43 Amps of LV§f Through this cable over a distance of §45 blocks§f from the source to the machine that's using the power.
S-----M

You should theoretically be transferring §496 EU/t(3A*32)§f if the cable was §4lossless§f. but you're not, so you will have to account for the loss as well. 

The formula for Net Loss:
§4Net Loss = Loss Constant*Current*Distance§f

§4Loss Constant§f: The Loss/Ampere/Meter value written in the cable's tooltip, differs between different materials, in the case of a Tin Cable it is 1
§4Current§f: Current flowing through cable, in this case it is 3 Amps
§4Distance§f: Distance between the source and the machine, in this case it is 5 Blocks, Note that it has to be accounted individually for each unique machine and source, als§4§fo§4 inactive machines/sources do not count§f.
So using our formula we can calculate that our Net Loss here is §43*1*5 = 15 EU/t§f
That means that instead of transferring 96 EU/t we are actually transferring §481 EU/t§f. Yikes, that is a §418.5%§f Loss Rate

To avoid this you can have your §4generators(power sources) closer to your machines§f, Alternatively you can decrease the amount of Current drawn by transforming your power up to a high tier, this way you will draw §44 times less amperes per voltage tier you transform up§f,§f you can then transform the power down to the tier you need it in near your machines.
You can also just use a §4different cable material§f.
Coating wires with rubber will also remove some of their power loss.

You can also turn EU directly into RF/FE by connecting a GT cable to an RF consumer, it does so in a §41:4 ratio§f from EU to RF.

§4Note: You do not need to understand all of this to be able to use GT power effectively, but once you get to know these mechanics, they can become quite fun challenges to calculate your power plans.§f

Not quite a dummy anymore ey?

§4The Trash Compactor§f is a very big multiblock that can be used to Compact and Compress things together.

You can also use it to turn ingots into plates with a §43:2§f ratio.

You can now replicate life!

As you run this, you'll need to keep the Crystal Glass free from contaminants by scraping clean any §a§4Bio Covered Glass§r that shows up by a GT §3§4Knife§f§f.

The §a§4Bio-Goo§r collected this way is quite useful for a few processes.

If the Glass is replaced with §d§4Purple Crystal Glass§r, it will not need cleaning.

You will also get §4Sludge§f as a byproduct, you can use a §4Sludge Refinery§f to turn the sludge into differnet earthly materials.

You can process§4 Cave Roots§f Fabricated from the Bio-Organic Fabricator into some pretty useful stuff.

Recycle it to get §4Cave Root Dust§f.

Either let the dust soak in Water to become §4Cave Root Pulp§f or Compact it for it to turn into §4Cave Root Plates§f, You can further process that to get a §4Circuit Boar§fd.

You can also Compact the Cave Root Pulp into§4 Cave Root Paper§f, Which is useful for making §4Resistors§f.

With your circuits you can now make a §4Careful Assemblicator§f.

You will need some glass from the Station for this.

If you want to use it to make LV Machines, you will have to §4Overclock§f the multiblock to LV tier by adding another ULV Energy Hatch to the multiblock. It will accept 4 Amps of ULV Energy which is equal to 1 Amp of LV; allowing it to operate LV Recipes.
This is possible because each Energy Hatch can accept §4up to 2 Amps§f.

With your NASA Slow Cooker you can create a very useful chemical known as §4Sulfuric Acid§f.

First mix some Sulfur Dust with some Oxygen, That will give you §4Sulfur Dioxide§f(SO2).
If you now add some more Oxygen to the mix it will result in §4Sulfur Trioxide§f(SO3).
Lastly add some Water and it will result in §4Sulfuric Acid§f(H2SO4).

Sulfuric Acid has a lot of uses, if you mix it with different colors of Crystal Dust it will yield different fluids§f. Then either Heat or Cool the fluids to get some new Materials; §aLow Covalence Dust§f, §cFirestone §f& §9Reactive Crystal Powder§f.

§4Note§f: Since §4Sulfuric Acid§f is an Acid, A Bronze Drum cannot handle it, you'll have to use §9Steel Drums§r or §4EIO Fluid Tanks§f to store it.

§4The Sludge Refinery§f is a machine that can turn Sludge Waste from the Bio-Organic Fabricator into useful materials.

It consumes 10 RF/t & turns 1000L of sludge into a random earthly materials once in 20 ticks.

This is every §4Filosopher's best friend§f(get it?).

It is needed to turn Redstone blocks into §4Glowstone§f and also turn Coal dust into §4Sulfur dust§f.

You can even use it to turn Tough Hulls into White Tough Hulls & turn Sturdy Hulls to Light Hulls if you are ever running low on §4Silver/Steel/Iron/Copper§f.

The §6Suit Jetpack§f is a very fine addition to your Space Suit, You can put it in your Space Suit using the Suit Workbench, It will also need an additional §7Pressure Tank §fto work.

It uses §9Hydrogen to work, you can charge it with §9Hydrogen§f just like you can charge your space suit with Oxygen.

Hold Space to fly up.

One of Firestone's uses is making a §4Sintering Furnace§f.

This furnace provides §4Free and Faster Smelting§f§r §r§4from Smelting 9 dust to a block in just 16 seconds§f and can also turn §4Dust to Rods with a 2:3 ratio§f.

You can replace the Glass with §4Purple Crystal Glass§f to avoid Bio-Covered Glass and maintenance on the Bio-Organic Fabricator.

Just like the Silver Exhaust vent you can only have 1 of these on the multiblock and it will work just fine.

You can use the §aBio-Goo§f waste you get from the Bio-Organic Fabricator for some useful stuff.

You can smelt it to get §6Sticky Resin§f.

You can analyze it in the §eAnalyzer§f to get a variety of stuff, most importantly §aGrass§f, §aSlime Balls§f & §dRabbit DNA§f which can be used to get leather.

It's time for you to make §4Circuit Components§f.
§4§f
You will need §4Carbon Dust§f for making Resistors, I hope you have been keeping your NASA Slow Cooker clean for this!

It is highly recommended to go for a §4Sintering Furnace§f and/or use a §4Trash Compactor§f to make your Rods & Plates for the sheer amount of resources you'll need for this.

It is also very useful to §4batchcraft§f the circuits instead of making few at a time. Though you should've learnt the GT Drill by now.
Well done! You have now finished the first chapter of the modpack, let's see how well you'll do in the next.

The Cubocentric Crystallizer will grow a crystal from tiny piles of Crystal dust, No more waiting for the Recycler!

You should make a profit from this real fast.
Make an LV Centrifuge to process §4Asteroid Rock Dust§f into various materials, Albeit very slow it can be very worth it in later stages of the game.

§4Exploration§f is very worth it in most stages of the game and is a big part of this pack, By exploration, you can find different §4Structures§f and loot them, giving yourself a huge advantage if you're lucky. 

You can also mine some §4asteroids§f to get ores, asteroid dust etc.

You can process the asteroid dust later in the station for good yield.

To prepare the area for launching the rocket you will have to make a §4Launch Site§f.

A Launch Site includes;
A Launch Pad,
A Structure Tower to support the rocket,
A Rocket Assembling Machine to assemble your rocket.

§4The Launch Pad§f is made of Launch Pad blocks in a Horizontal Rectangular/Square shape. You will probably need a 5x5 Launch Pad.

§4The Structure Tower§k§f consists of a Vertical Tower of Structure Tower Blocks. The first Structure Tower Block needs to be at the same level as your Launch Pad Blocks, The last one should be at the same level as the top of your rocket, You will probably need 8 Structure Towers.

Now you can place your §4Rocket Assembling Machine§f, one block out and a block up from your Launch Pad, facing away from the Launch Site.

Make sure to clear out any space above your rocket to allow it to rise.

Your Rocket could look however you want it to look like, but there are some §4rules§f;

Make sure your Monopropellant Fuel Engines are on the bottom of the rocket.

Make sure you have a Guidance Computer in the rocket.

Make sure your rocket isn't too heavy or else it will not be able to Lift Off.

Make sure you have enough fuel tanks on the rocket to ensure a clear landing.

The current amount of fuel tanks and engines in the quest should be able to make a rocket lift off.

Once you're done building the rocket open the §4Assembling Machine§f and Click on §6Scan§f, If there is anything wrong with the rocket it will tell you.
If the rocket is fine, you should be able to Click on §6Build§f, and it will turn your Rocket Structure to an actual rocket.

Now you should fuel the rocket with your 4 Buckets of §4Rocket Fuel§f, Simply right click on the rocket with the buckets to fill it with fuel.

Now the only thing left to do is to set §4A Destination§f, Shift-Right Click on the rocket to open it's GUI, Place your §4Planet ID Chip§e§f inside the Guidance Computer, And Click §6Select Dst§f in the main menu of the rocket, Choose the planet you wish to go to and press §6Select§f on the top left.

Take a seat in the rocket and...

§4Liftoff!
This version is expensive, so you'll want to unlock the next generation of MV Curcuit as soon as possible.

While you are in the §2Betweenlands§r, and especially while in the water, you and any tools you are holding will slowly start to decay, as shown by the brownish bar above your hunger. If it goes low enough, you'll start to lose max health until you're at 3 hearts and will be slowed, while tools will preform worse Until they are unable to function.

Eating these removes some decay.

Killing these can be a great way to get a backpack or a decent set of armor!

The Betweenlands is a dangerous place, filled with lots of critters that want to eat you, enough swampland to last a lifetime, and intricate Dungeons with fantastic loot and challanging bosses!

§aThis Planet will put your adventuring skills to the test!

This gem like material is used to craft Vials for Potions.

Can be found inside of Giant Weedwood Trees found uncommonly in Swamplands, Coarse Islands, and Marsh biomes,
After dropping some Moss on a placed Peat block, hold right click with the Octine Ingot in order to light it on fire.

In order to create an §dInfusion§r, you'll first need to feed your pet §6Gecko§r some §aground down items§r to discover §eAspects§r.

Once you've collected information on many items, you'll be able to select an Elixir to make. We'll take the §dElixir of Healing§r as an example.

Looking at the page for §dElixir of Healing§r§r in your §bHerblore Book§r, you'll see that it requires the §cYeowynn§r and §2Ordaniss§r aspects.

Collect some items containing these aspects, and we'll start getting the §6Infuser§r ready.

The §6Infuser§r needs to be above Smoldering Peat, which you can ignite by dropping moss on a Peat block and using an §eOctine Ingot §ron it. You'll also need up to 3 buckets of Swamp Water inside. Once its heated up, you'll start to see the Evaporation timer rising. If this gets to maximum before you stir it, you'll lose a bucket of what's inside.

Place up to 6 items inside, then left click to stir. If you made a valid recipe it will show up on the right, and will take quite a while to stir into a working §dInfusion§r. If it doesn't make a valid recipe it will be quite quick. A shower of bubbles and a change of color signifies its safe to remove the §dInfusion§r with a bucket or 3. 

Once you've got your bucket of §dInfusion§r, you'll be wanting to turn it into a usable product. The next step is simple, place it into an Alembic and wait! Once you don't see any more particles you can extract it with §eDentrothyst Vials§r.

If you brewed an Elixir recipe, you'll get that with variable strength and durablity based on the amounts of aspect you added. If not, you'll get Vials filled with purifed aspects, which have various uses.

If an §dInfusion§r completely evaporates, a §bShallowbreath§r will spawn! These are quite dangerous and will try to smother you. Be sure to have a source of health regen, and some §6Vials§r. Attacking it with an empty §6Vial§r will fill it after a few swings.
This can be used to light Moss on fire by holding right click.

Trimming a Bubbler Crab or Silt Crab results in 2 Crab Claws and 2 Crabsticks.

Shift right click with an Amphibious Armor piece in hand to access the armor piece’s upgrade menu. The Helmet and Boots have 3 slots, while the Chestplate and Leggings have 5 slots. Adding multiple of the same upgrade makes that upgrade stronger.

Use a Biopathic Trigger or Toggle to activate or toggle the upgrades. 


§3Upgrages:§r

Electric Upgrade §dChestplate§r Zaps attackers or nearby mobs for up to 5 damage per mob.

Glide Upgrade §dChestplate§r Sprint in air to glide.

Urchin Spike Upgrade §dChestplate§r Attacks enemies with urchin spikes for up to 10 damage.

Fish Vortex Upgrade §dChestplate§r Raises enemies in the air.

Snot §dChestplate§r Increases underwater mining speed.

Ascent Upgrade §9Leggings§r Leap up to 10 blocks out of the water by sneaking on the floor for 1 second.

Anadia Eye §aHelmet§r Applies Night Vision underwater.

Glowing Goop §aHelmet§r Highlights Anadia up to 25 blocks away.

Anadia Gills §aHelmet§r/§dChestplate§r Extends water breathing time.

Anadia Swim Bladder §dChestplate§r/§9Leggings§r Increases swim speed when moving up or down.

Lurker Skin §dChestplate§r/§9Leggings§r Increases knockback resistance chance.

Anadia Fins §dChestplate/Leggings§r/§cBoots§r Increases swim speed.

Anadia Scales §6Any§r Adds 0.5 Armor per slot.

This can also repair your tools of corrosion.

This battle will be quite challanging! You'll need to hit the large face on the side of the trunk, while avoiding lots of special attacks.

The difficulty can be tweaked by adjusting the amount of wisps on the pedestals, with harder fights offering more rewards.

§eSpores§r are a common drop from §eSporelings§r, which spawn on Shelf Fungus. Most commonly found on Giant Roots in the Coarse Islands biome.

Can be found most commonly in the Sludge Plains underwater. The ore glows at night, making it fairly easy to spot.

These can be used to augment weapons, and some tools and armor.
Use one of these on a Menhir to link it.
This will help you find landmarks and bosses.

Most importantly at this point, you can also feed it §bCompost§r in exchange for§e Sap Spit§r!

Each floor will have a §6Door Code §ron the stair down. This consists of 3 horizantal rows randomized to create a unique pattern. In order to unlock the next floor, you'll need to change the lock on the Door down§r to match the pattern at the beginning of the floor.

Pyrads are tree spirits that can spawn around Giant Weedwood Trees and from Monster Spawners in Cragrock Towers and the Wight Fortress. 

If found around Giant Weedwood Trees, Pyrads are passive innitially. If damaged enough, a block is taken from their tree, or if its night time, they will become active and try to attack. 

If killed during their fireball chargeup time, they have achance to drop §cPyrad Flames§r.
Ash Sprites have a chance to spawn when breaking §dUrns of Chance§r.
Crypt Crawlers spawn on the 6th level of the Labyrinth and can drop a variety of loot.

Effects:

Sap Ball: (1 item to fill, lasts indefinitely, but duration depletes by half per decay point restored) Emits a small brown puff and slowly heals Decay in a large area (32x18x32).

Weeping Blue Petal: (1 item to fill, lasts indefinitely, but duration depletes by 1/6th per 2 decay points restored) Emits a small blue puff and slowly heals decay in a large area (32x18x32).

Plant Tonic: (1 item to fill, 10 minute duration when full) Emits a small brown cloud and prevents crops from decaying and removes existing decay in a medium area (16x5x16).

Elixir: (1 item to fill, 16 minute duration when full) Emits a small cloud the colour of the Elixir and continuously applies a weak version of the Elixir, with a duration of 14 seconds (regardless of the Elixir's duration) in a large area. Potency affects range (default at level 1 is 32x18x32).

Stagnant Water: (1 item to fill, 25 minute duration when full) Emits a thick yellow-green fog and continuously applies the Elixir of Decay effect, causing Decay to be accelerated in a small area (13x2x13).

Bottled Fog: (8 items to fill, 120 minute duration when full) Emits a thick white fog and increases crop growth and allows Sludgeon plants to grow in a small area (13x2x13). Stackable.

Aspect: (5 aspect levels to fill [must be combined in 1 bottle], 90 minute duration when full) Emits a thick fog of the aspect's colour and infuses Aspectrus crops with the aspect, also enabling them to grow in a small area (13x3x13).

Cremains: (1 item to fill, 2.5 minute duration when full) Emits a dark red cloud and sets fire to any living creature in a small area, causing them to drop 0-2 cremains upon death, along with their usual on-fire drops (13x13x13).

Swamp Water: (8 items to fill, 60 minute duration when full. Duration only decreases when Bark Amulet is added) Emits a cloud of white steam that carries the effect of the item it is imbued with in a large area (~48x_x48?).
        Can be imbued with a Bark Amulet. For that, place the Bark Amulet in the left slot, then right-click the Censer with a Swamp Water Bucket. It will show the life of the mobs the same way as it would do if you were wearing it.
You'll be able to collect Fog in Vials while on the 6th & 7th floors. When used in a Censer, it boosts nearby plant growth.

If burned in a Censor, will remove and prevent decay.
